println(string, *args, **kwargs)

Function to output the println string for the C_AOS module. Called via the visitors when reaching a println statement in user code.

For the C_AOS module this is a call to printf, using the string argument as the formatted string with a line end, and the *args contains any C values used in the formatted string.

Parameters

  • string (str) – The formatted string to use with printf.

  • current_indent (int) – The current indentation level

  • *args –

    A list of strings containing the C values required for output.

set_io_modules(input_module, output_module)

Function to set the IO Modules. Called from HartreeParticleDSL helper functions instead of directly by the user.

Parameters

  • input_module (HartreeParticleDSL.backends.C_AOS.C_AOS_IO_Mixin.C_AOS_IO_Mixin or None) – The IO module to use for input from file.

  • ouput_module – The IO module to use for input from file.

Raises

InvalidIOModuleError – if either input_module or output_module are not implementing the C_AOS_IO_Mixin class
